{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Konstruktor","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Glossary/Constructor","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>Ein <strong>Konstruktor</strong>&nbsp;gehört zu einer Instanz eines&nbsp;bestimmten Klassen-<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Object\">Objekts</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Der Konstrutktor instanziiert dieses Objekt und bietet Zugriff auf seine privaten Informationen. Das Konzept des Konstruktors findet&nbsp;in den meisten&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/OOP\">Objekt-orientierten Programmiersprachen</a> Anwendung. Im Allgemeinen wird ein Konstruktor in&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a> in der Instanz einer&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Class\">Klasse</a> deklariert.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// This is a generic default constructor class Default</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">Default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// This is an overloaded constructor class Overloaded</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// with parameter arguments</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">Overloaded</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">arg1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> arg2<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token operator\">...</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>argN</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>Um einen Konstruktor aufzurufen, verwenden Sie den <code>new</code> operator, welcher einer&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Variable\">Variable</a> eine neue&nbsp;<a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Object_reference\">Objekt-Referenz <small>(en-US)</small></a> zuweist.</p>\n\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">Default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// A new reference of a Default object assigned to a</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// local variable defaultReference</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> defaultReference <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Default</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"generelles_wissen","title":"Generelles Wissen","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a title=\"Konstruktor\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Constructor_%28object-oriented_programming%29\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Konstruktor</a> auf&nbsp;Wikipedia</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"technische_referenz","title":"Technische Referenz","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Learn/JavaScript/Objects#the_constructor\">The constructor in object oriented programming for JavaScript</a> on MDN</li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/new\">New operator in JavaScript</a> on MDN</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Ein Konstruktor gehört zu einer Instanz eines bestimmten Klassen-Objekts.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Constructor","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Constructor","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Constructeur","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Constructor (コンストラクター)","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Конструктор","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Constructor","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"建構子","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/glossary/constructor","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/glossary/constructor/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/Glossary","title":"Glossar"},{"uri":"/de/docs/Glossary/Constructor","title":"Konstruktor"}],"pageTitle":"Konstruktor - Glossar | MDN","noIndexing":false}}